<h1>Thai Chop Salad</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<h3>Salad</h3>
<ul>
<li>1/2 medium green cabbage (3 cups), finely chopped</li>
<li>1/2 medium purple cabbage (3 cups), finely chopped</li>
<li>1/2 cucumber (1 cup), diced</li>
<li>1 red bell pepper (1 cup), diced</li>
<li>2 medium carrots (1 cup), shredded</li>
<li>1/2 bunch cilantro (1/2 cup), chopped</li>
<li>1 cup tofu, air fried (substitute beans of your choice)</li>
<li>1/2 cup roasted peanuts, chopped</li>
</ul>
<h3>Dressing</h3>
<ul>
<li>3 tablespoons soy sauce</li>
<li>1/2 cup peanut butter</li>
<li>1 teaspoon sriracha</li>
<li>2 tablespoons rice vinegar</li>
<li>1 tablespoon lime juice</li>
<li>2 tablespoons water</li>
<li>1 tablespoon toasted sesame oil</li>
<li>1 tablespoon maple syrup</li>
<li>1 teaspoon ginger, grated</li>
<li>1 teaspoon garlic, minced</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
<li>Mix together dressing ingredients until combined.</li>
<li>Toss all ingredients with dressing.</li>
<li>Enjoy.</li>
</ol>
